The next most powerful markets were Adelaide, Brisbane and Darwin, where prices rose by an average of five to six percent.
At the other end of the scale was Canberra, which saw government spending cuts, where prices rose just 1.4 percent in a year.
Mr Lawless said that now that spring has begun, there will be an increase in the number of properties for sale over the next few months, which will be a &quot;real test&quot; for the market.
