As for the Ukrainian events, they themselves and the reaction of the leadership of Belarus to them only spurred this process.
On the one hand, Minsk managed to maintain relations with Ukraine - warm enough not to lose much in mutual trade, and President Poroshenko could come to Belarus for negotiations.
On the other hand, the Belarusian leader, who de jure did not recognize the annexation of Crimea to Russia and called for punishing pro-Russian militias in Donbass with all severity, did not quarrel with Moscow either.
