According to Russian news reports of his remarks, Russian President Vladimir Putin demanded on Sunday that the Ukrainian government stop fighting separatists in the east of the country and immediately begin negotiations on the &quot;statehood&quot; of the breakaway region.
His spokesman, Dmitry Peskov, later made it clear that Putin did not mean to hint that separatist-controlled eastern Ukrainian territory would become part of Russia, but that its status within Ukraine needed to be revised to give the Russian-speaking region an opportunity to defend its rights and interests.
